2.Name: Algorithm to derive ADADAS.ADY
2.Description:
ADY = ADT - TRTSDT + 1, if ADT>=TRTSDT. ADY = 
ADT - TRTSDT, if ADT<TRTSDT.

3.Name: Algorithm to derive ADADAS.ANL01FL
3.Description: If multiple visits fall into the same visit window, then the one closest to the target date is chosen for analysis. These are flagged with ANL01FL="Y".

5.Name: Algorithm to derive ADADAS.AVAL.ACTOT
5.Description: Sum of ADAS scores for items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13, and 14, see SAP section 14.2 for details on adjusting for missing values

6.Name: Algorithm to derive ADADAS.AVISIT
6.Description: Derived based on windowing algorithm described in SAP, Section 8.2

10.Name: Algorithm to derive ADADAS.DTYPE
10.Description: Set to "LOCF" if a record is imputated when PARAMCD="ACTOT"; otherwise, set to missing

13.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.ADURU
13.Description: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAYS'

23.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AENDT
23.Description: AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date

24.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AENDY
24.Description: IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

44.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCC01FL
44.Description: Subset to CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL=?Y?) within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)

45.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCC02FL
45.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL=?Y?) within each Subject

46.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCC03FL
46.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL=?Y?) within each Subject and SOC

47.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCC04FL
47.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL=?Y?) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

48.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCCFL
48.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL=?Y?) within each Subject

49.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCCPFL
49.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL=?Y?) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

50.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.AOCCSFL
50.Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL=?Y?) within each Subject and SOC

51.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.ASTDT
51.Description: AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.

52.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.ASTDTF
52.Description: ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study.

53.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.ASTDY
53.Description: IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

54.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.CQ01NAM
54.Description: If AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBC UTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

63.Name: Algorithm to derive ADAE.TRTEMFL
63.Description: If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

69.Name: Algorithm to derive ADLBC.AENTMTFL
69.Description: Last observed value for this lab parameter during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject

71.Name: Algorithm to derive ADLBC.ANL01FL
71.Description: If ALBTRVAL  = max(ALBTRVAL) then ANL01FL is 'Y'

72.Name: Algorithm to derive ADLBC.ANRIND
72.Description: if AVAL < [0.5*LBSTNRLO) then ANRIND = 'Y' else if AVAL > [0.5*LBSTRNHI),'H','N'

73.Name: Algorithm to derive ADLBC.AVISIT
73.Description: Last observed value for this lab parameter during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject

75.Name: Algorithm to derive ADLBC.BNRIND
75.Description: if BASE < [0.5*LBSTNRLO) then ANRIND = 'Y' else if BASE > [0.5*LBSTRNHI),'H','N'

89.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.AGEGR1N
89.Description: AGEGR1 = 1 if AGE <65. AGEGR1 = 2 if AGE 65-80. AGEGR1 = 3 if AGE >80.

94.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.BMIBLGR1
94.Description:
BMIBLGR1="<25" if . < BMIBL <25.
BMIBLGR1="25-<30" if 25 <=BMIBL <30.
BMIBLGR1=">=30"if BMIBL >=30.

95.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.COMP16FL
95.Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=10 and ENDDT>=date of visit 10, N otherwise

96.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.COMP24FL
96.Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=12 and ENDDT>= date of visit 12 , N otherwise

97.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.COMP8FL
97.Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=8 and ENDDT >= date of visit 8, N otherwise

98.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.CUMDOSE
98.Description: For ARMN=0 or 1: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDUR. --- For ARMN=2: CUMDOSE will be based on 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 1st dosing interval (i.e., visit4date-TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subj discontinued <=visit 4 and > visit 3), 81mg per day for the # of days subj was in 2nd dosing interval (i.e., visit12date-visit4date if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT-visit4date if subj discontinued <= visit 12 and > visit 4), and 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 3rd dosing interval (i.e., TRTEDT - visit12date if subj continued after visit 12).

100.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.DCREASCD
100.Description: Grouping of DCDECOD values to support summarizing study completion status and reason for discontinuation

102.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.DISONSDT
102.Description: MH.MHSTDTC where MHCAT='PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS' converted to SAS date

103.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.DSRAEFL
103.Description: Y if DCREASCD='Adverse Event'. Null otherwise

105.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.DURDIS
105.Description: number of months between VISIT1DT and DISONSET

108.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.EFFFL
108.Description: Y if SAFFL='Y AND subject has at least one record in QS for ADAS-Cog with VISITNUM>3 AND at least one record in QS for CIBIC+ with VISITNUM>3, N otherwise

109.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.EOSSTT
109.Description: COMPLETED if ADSL.DCDECOD='COMPLETED'. DISCONTINUED if ADSL.DCDECOD not equal to COMPLETED.

112.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.ITTFL
112.Description: Y if ARMCD ne ' '. N otherwise

113.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.MMSETOT
113.Description: sum of QS.QSORRES values for the subject when QSCAT = MINI-MENTAL STATE

119.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.SAFFL
119.Description: Y if ITTFL='Y' and TRTSDT ne missing. N otherwise

121.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.SITEGR1
121.Description: refer to SAP, Section 7.1 - if not pooled then SITEGR1=SITEID. If pooled, SITEGR1 will be 900

124.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.TRT01A
124.Description: TRT01A=TRT01P, i.e., no difference between actual and randomized treatment in this study.

125.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.TRT01AN
125.Description: Numeric code for TRT01A which corresponds to the randomized dose

127.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.TRT01PN
127.Description: Numeric code for TRT01P which corresponds to the randomized dose

129.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.TRTEDT
129.Description: The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.

130.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.TRTSDT
130.Description: SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=3, converted to SAS date

131.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.VISIT1DT
131.Description: SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=1, converted to SAS date

132.Name: Algorithm to derive ADSL.VISNUMEN
132.Description: if DS.VISITNUM=13 where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED' then VISNUMEN=12, otherwise VISNUMEN=DS.VISITNUM where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED'

134.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.ADT
134.Description: if ADAE.ASTDT is not missing and occurred after TRTSDT then ADAE.ASTDT else convert ADSL.RFENDTC to a SAS numeric date

136.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.CNSR
136.Description: if ADAE.TRTEMFL ="Y" then CNSR=0, else CNSR=1

137.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.EVNTDESC
137.Description: if ADTTE.CNSR = 0 then "Dematologic Event Occured", else if ADTTE.CNSR =1 then "Study Completion Date"

140.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.SRCDOM
140.Description: The Source domain referred to in order to populate ADT (either ADAE or ADSL)

141.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.SRCSEQ
141.Description: The value of ADAE.AESEQ if SRCDOM=ADAE, otherwise null.

142.Name: Algorithm to derive ADTTE.SRCVAR
142.Description: The Source variable referred to in order to populate ADT (either ASTDT or RFENDT)
